                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d236">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/1169: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Special Representative of the President</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-04-07T13:00:00-06:00"
                            >April 7, 1938—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>64. At the meeting of the Commission this morning the Nicaraguan delegation
                    agreed with the Commission to a recess. At tomorrow’s session the attitude of
                    the Honduran delegation will be ascertained and if favorable an act will be
                    signed that afternoon by the two delegations and the Commission suspending the
                    plenary sessions for a period of 2 months.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Corrigan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
